2.caption: 1975 Major League Baseball All-Star Game
2.description: The 1975 Major League Baseball All-Star Game was the 46th midseason exhibition between the all-stars of the American League (AL) and the National League (NL), the two leagues comprising Major League Baseball. The game was played on July 15, 1975, at Milwaukee County Stadium in Milwaukee, Wisconsin, home of the Milwaukee Brewers of the American League. The game resulted in a 6–3 victory for the NL.
2.inspected:MVP: Bill Madlock and Jon Matlack (CHC, NYM[2])
2.inspected:TV announcers: Curt Gowdy, Joe Garagiola and Tony Kubek
